sub_title: Student at Erasmus University Rotterdam                   |BSc International Bachelor Economics & Business Economics
summary: As an economics student at Erasmus University Rotterdam, I am driven to understand the complexities of global economics and how they shape businesses and societies. With a strong foundation in economic theory and a passion for staying up-to-date on current trends, I aim to make a meaningful impact in my future career. I am skilled in data analysis, problem-solving, and critical thinking, and I am eager to apply these skills to real-world economic challenges. At the university, I have been involved in various student organizations and initiatives, and I have developed strong communication and teamwork skills. I am always seeking opportunities to grow, learn, and make valuable connections, and I believe that my education and experiences at Erasmus University will serve as a strong foundation for my future career.

projects: [{'title': 'Nano Emulsive Eco diesel.', 'date': {'start': {'month': 10, 'day': None, 'year': 2018}, 'end': {'month': 3, 'day': None, 'year': 2020}}, 'description': 'The name of our project is NANO EMULSIVE ECO-DIESEL. It started as a school project but continued to prosper. It is fact that 80% of all toxic emission gases are from cars that’s why we want to introduce you new type of fuel will help to reduce amount of  harmful exhaust emission gasses as NOx, SOx and carbon monoxide. This new fuel is made by mixing of ethanol with diesel with the help of emulsifier. The use of ethanol in diesel engines has a number of possible\nbenefits. It has been found that it has an impact on reducing the  high temperature in engine and reduces the NOX and carbon monoxide emissions. Furthermore, the technique was developed to improve the thermal efficiency and reduce exhaust emissions, or used as the safety fuel. The commercial diesel which is emulsified with oxygen-containing compounds decreases NOx emission as a result of increased surface area of diesel droplets .This project will help to reduce air pollution which is one of the aims of Kiyoto protocol.', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Alasgar', 'last_name': 'Sadigov', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Student at Erasmus University Rotterdam                   |BSc International Bachelor Economics & Business Economics'}]}]
